----
'''Origin'''
Chibor a rare a misterious creature often found running from ukrainian women in their 50's wearing head scarfs carrying brooms. They oust the dreaded Chibor by shouting "Chibor!" in a high pitch while waving their brooms frantically. In the 1990's Chibor moved to the UK where he still holds residence today.

----
'''Diet'''
The Chibor often consumes vast quantites of milk, as in the Ukraine he often drank milk from stray dogs roaming the land. Chibor's favourate food is meat. He often ingests this food while singing, "Meat me at the crossroads!"

----

Although he fools many around him the RGM (Rose Garden Mob) knows exactly who he is and is planning to send him back to the Ukraine to be beaten to death by old women. Because of his bad experience with people in the past, Chibor tries to avoid conflict by saying "Chibor is sorry" often repeating this phrase for maximum effect. An old Greek proverb says "If you see a Chibor run for the hills, before it messes up everything in your life!"
----
Currently Chibor owns "Chibor inter-bank" which is guarded by the highly respected "Chang-yaing" guards.